<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-037-067 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 465 365</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Oct 10 1991 v17 n21 p75(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Borland intros design tool for non-programmers. (ResourceWorkshop)(brief article) (Software) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Borland International Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    BORL.andO;Product:   Resource Workshop (Program development software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionProgram development software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SCOTTS VALLEY, Calif.andP;  -- Borland International Inc. is shipping ResourceWorkshop, a design tool aimed at enabling developers of Windows applicationsto create professional-looking user interfaces or customize existingapplications.andM;The product can be used to visually create a customize Windows resources suchas icons, dialogs, fonts and bitmap graphics without writing code.andP;  Acollection of 64 graphical icons is included with each package.andM;Features include: an integrated resource manager with graphics-orientedresource editors; custom controls, which include radio buttons and checkboxes, push buttons and dialog boxes; ease-of-use for non-programmers; anduser-defined resources.andM;The Resource Workshop is available for IBM and compatible PCs running Windows3.0 and higher.andP;  It is priced at $49.95 (U.S.).andO;</TEXT></DOC>